	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The Lambent Stones are required for all Lambent armor pieces.  If you look under &quot;Temple of Solusek Ro&quot; in the geography section of this site there is a link for the Lambent Armor quest.  It is a comlete spoiler, so unless you want all the info don't go.  The Lambent Armor is bard only, so if you get a stone, I'm sure any bard out there will be interested in purchasing it.  You can combine the Lambent Stones with various other gems by giving it to the person that gives out the quest, but you get another gem that is used for the Lambent Armor piece you are trying to get, so unless you are a bard, I wouldn't bother, unless you want to sell that to a bard.  In my opinion it is not worth the trouble because the bard will have to go there anyway to get the armor, so you are really not saving them any time.  If you really want to go to the trouble to combine the Lambent Stone with the necessary gems, you may as well complete the quest and sell the Lambent Armor piece that you get.  Those can sell for lots of platinum, depending on which piece you have.  I am not sure if this will increase your faction with 415, but if you kill Dervish Cutthroats and turn the rings to an Orc named Ortallius in the NW corner of South Ro you will increase your faction with the Temple of Solusek Ro.  Hope this helped.
				</font>
